      "structural_role": "Curator macro iterates response.curator.exhibits, filtering by position attribute. Two render modes per exhibit: simple message (`<blockquote class='blockquote search-exhibit'>`) when exhibit.messageHtml is set, or full listing-item card (`<article class='listing-item listing-item--promoted'>`) when exhibit.descriptionHtml is set. The card carries a lowercase `<span class='listing-item__promoted-tag'>promoted</span>` label. Three position contexts in partial.ftl: left (in sidebar L192), top (above results L222), bottom (below results L229). Best-bets-vs-curator distinction via exhibit.category=='BEST_BETS' (HasBestBets, HasCurator macros) \u2014 but those filtering macros are not invoked from partial.ftl, only HasCuratorOrBestBet is.",
      "macros_defined": [
