      "markup_defect": "L31: `<article class='listing-item listing-item--promoted listing-item--background-grey10 listing-item--color-black' ${(exhibit.additionalProperties.class)!}\">` \u2014 stray `\"` after the class binding. The expression produces `<article class='listing-item ...' SOMECLASS\">` which is invalid HTML attribute syntax. Browsers will likely tolerate but the trailing `\"` ends up as literal output.",
