    {
      "id": "inactive-renderer-imports-aggregate-one-line",
      "source_layer": "FUNNELBACK_PARTIAL",
      "source_layer_detail": "results.video.ftl, results.facebook.ftl, results.events.ftl, results.twitter.ftl, results.instagram.ftl (bodies not read per brief stop rules)",
      "modifiability": {
        "who_controls": "Vic-controlled FTL"
      },
      "structural_role": "Imported by partial.ftl L75-79. Each exposes a Result macro (and presumably ListView/CardView/GenericView per the established pattern). Reachable only via the renderer-dispatch entry point in result_list.ftl if profile config stencils.template.result.<collection> names one of these namespaces AND results from that collection exist in the response packet.",
      "status": "DEAD_IMPORT per Vic's confirmation that no crawler feeds these content types on SU's collection set.",
      "rebuild_implication": "The new system drops these renderer paths. The four active renderers (news, law, programs, people) are the live set.",
      "related_findings": [
        "E17",
        "E28"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "findings": [
    {
      "id": "E1",
      "category": "DEAD_IMPORT",
      "title": "partial.ftl imports curator.ftl twice",
      "evidence": "partial.ftl:44 `<#import \"curator.ftl\" as curator />` and partial.ftl:54 `<#import \"curator.ftl\" as curator />` \u2014 same template, same alias, two import statements.",
      "implication": "FreeMarker <#import> is idempotent so the duplicate is not a runtime defect. Structurally it is a copy/paste residue and a clean trim candidate for the rebuild's import block. Provisional in brief v1.1; confirmed at E.2 execution."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "AfterSearchOnly gate asymmetry \u2014 six macros sit outside the gate",
      "evidence": "partial.ftl L221-233: `<@s.AfterSearchOnly>` wraps curator-top + no_results + result_list + curator-bottom. OUTSIDE the gate: search_tools.SearchTools (L214), query_blending.QueryBlending (L216), spelling_suggestions.SpellingSuggestions (L217), facets_breadcrumbs.Breadcrumb (L218), pagination.Pagination (L235), contextual_navigation.ContextualNavigation (L236). Each of these macros has its own internal guard (counts.Counts is content-conditional, QueryBlending is QSups-gated, SpellingSuggestions is spell-gated, facets.breadcrumbs is facetExtras.hasSelectedNonTabFacets-gated, pagination renders only stencils.pagination.{previous,pages,next} when present, contextual_navigation has HasContextualNavigation).",
      "implication": "The asymmetric gating is structurally functional thanks to per-macro internal guards. The rebuild can choose either to standardize one gate model (a uniform 'render only after search' wrapper) or to keep per-macro guards. The brief framed this around pagination and contextual_navigation specifically; the audit broadens the finding to all six. Provisional E2 in brief v1.1 is confirmed and extended."
    },
    {
      "id": "E3",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "hero_banner.SearchForm invokes Concierge, contains no Typeahead initialization",
      "evidence": "hero_banner.ftl:39 `<@concierge.Concierge />` inside SearchForm. No `$.typeahead({...})` call site in hero_banner.ftl. Concierge emits the autocomplete-concierge wrapper-div (per Phase C entry autocomplete-concierge-wrapper-div) and per-dataset spans.",
      "implication": "The active autocomplete pathway on the search-page hero is the autocomplete-concierge React component, NOT Twitter Typeahead. Combined with finding E11 (auto_complete namespace has zero invocations across all 27 in-scope templates), this closes Phase C Finding C8 definitively. Provisional E3 in brief v1.1 is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "id": "E4",
      "category": "UNUSED_FEATURE",
      "title": "Sessions subsystem is two-tiered; Tier 2 is wholly unwired",
      "evidence": "Tier 1: sessions.LastVisitedLink (sessions.ftl:11-20) is invoked from all five renderer files (results.ftl:108, results.law.ftl:109, results.news.ftl:123, results.people.ftl:114, results.programs.ftl:93). Gated by question.collection.configuration.valueAsBoolean('ui.modern.session') AND session AND session.getClickHistory(result.indexUrl). Tier 2: sessions.Controls (sessions.ftl:102-127), sessions.Configuration (L31-96), sessions.Templates (L135-146), sessions.ShortlistDrawer (L148-150), sessions.SearchHistoryAndShortlist (L22-25), sessions.ShortlistControl (L130-133). None of these are invoked from partial.ftl or any reached site. sessions.Controls is COMMENTED OUT at hero_banner.ftl:46. The shortlist drawer (sessions.shortlist.Drawer at L95-133), search history drawer (sessions.search_history.Drawer at L8-52), and the Funnelback.SessionCart JS init block (sessions.Configuration L36-94) all exist but never get emitted into the partial response. The TemplatesForResults macro (sessions.shortlist.ftl:79-86) that iterates .main namespaces for ShortlistTemplate-directives is the only consumer of per-renderer ShortlistTemplate macros, and it is transitively unreachable.",
      "implication": "Even if ui.modern.session is true (Vic profile-config inspection pending to confirm), only LastVisitedLink fires; the broader shortlist + search-history UX is wired-but-unsurfaced. If ui.modern.session is false, even LastVisitedLink is silent. Resolution: the rebuild design should explicitly decide which session features to keep. The Tier 2 macros plus the TemplatesForResults mechanism plus the per-renderer ShortlistTemplate macros (currently only results.news.ftl defines one, and it's a course-shaped template) are an entire feature-family unused in current production. Provisional E4 in brief v1.1 is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "id": "E5",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Phase A Finding F2 'Funnelback-partial-content' enumeration closes \u2014 each region linked to emitting template",
      "evidence": "Phase A v2's entry for funnelback-search-container-response-wrapper described the partial-content payload as 'tab bar + facets sidebar + results list + pagination + spelling + curator/best-bet slots \u2014 all PHASE E territory'. The E.2 partial.ftl body walk plus E.4 ancillary-template walks gives each region its emitter: tab bar = tabs.Tabs (partial.ftl:108); facets sidebar = facets.HasFacets+Facets (L184-189) plus curator-left (L192-194) plus tab-conditional CTA (L130-172); results column header = h2.sr-only 'Results' (L212); search tools = search_tools.SearchTools (L214); query blending notice = query_blending.QueryBlending (L216); spelling suggestion = spelling_suggestions.SpellingSuggestions (L217); facet breadcrumb = facets_breadcrumbs.Breadcrumb (L218); curator slots = curator.Curator at three positions (L192/L222/L229); no-results = no_results.NoResults (L226); results list = result_list.ResultList (L227); pagination = pagination.Pagination (L235); contextual navigation = contextual_navigation.ContextualNavigation (L236); SVG sprite = utilities.icons include (L92-94); main.js script tag = inline at L250.",
      "implication": "Phase A's F2 region enumeration is now backed by the FTL source line numbers and namespace+macro names. The rebuild's partial-response composition plan has a complete map: which region originates from which template, in what order, under what gating."
    },
    {
      "id": "E6",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "SVG sprite contract surface: 93 defined, 10 referenced from partial-response templates",
      "evidence": "utilities.icons.ftl defines 93 distinct `<symbol id='...'>` elements (full list in sprite_symbol_map.defined_symbols). Cross-reference of `<use href='#...'>` across all 27 in-scope templates yields 10 distinct symbol IDs in use: #add (6 sites), #close (6), #subtract (4), #information (2), #chevron (2), #time (1, unreachable), #overflow-menu (1), #no-results (1), #map (1, unreachable), #arrow (1).",
      "implication": "The partial-response sprite contract is small (10 symbols, 8 of them in reachable sites). The other 83 symbols are sized for a broader (potentially T4-PageLayout-driven) consumer surface or are legacy. The rebuild can substantially trim the sprite if the global consumer set (Phase D's PageLayout enumeration + FE-authored HTML + Squiz-stencils-HTML consumers) confirms they are unused. The partial-response-only subset documented here is necessary-but-not-sufficient to make a trim decision. Provisional E6 in brief v1.1 is confirmed and the symbol list is fully enumerated."
    },
    {
      "id": "E7",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "DOM id typo 'funnelbach' (not 'funnelback') on two anchor elements",
      "evidence": "partial.ftl:121 `<div class=\"funnelback-search__side ... cell\" id=\"funnelbach-search-facets\">` and partial.ftl:211 `<div class=\"funnelback-search__body ... cell\" id=\"funnelbach-search-body\">`. The class names use 'funnelback' correctly; the id values use 'funnelbach'. Likely typo at template authoring time.",
      "implication": "If FE/CSS selects on these element IDs, the selectors must spell the typo. If the typo IDs are unused selectors (CSS targets the class names; FE doesn't target the IDs), the typo has no consumer and is cosmetic-only. The Phase B FE-consumption audit will resolve whether anything in lib/, pages/, or public/ selects #funnelbach-search-facets or #funnelbach-search-body. The rebuild should standardize on 'funnelback' spelling and migrate any existing consumers."
    },
    {
      "id": "E8",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Brief CTA URL list contains '/directory' which does not appear in partial.ftl",
      "evidence": "Brief v1.1 E.2 section: 'four hardcoded URLs (/visit, /academics/all-programs, /directory, /newsroom)'. Actual partial.ftl L138-158 values: default '/visit', Programs '/academics/all-programs', Faculty & Staff 'https://redhawks.sharepoint.com/sites/Intranet-Home', News '/newsroom'. The Faculty & Staff branch does not target '/directory' \u2014 it targets an external SharePoint URL labeled 'Redhawk Hub' with button text 'Explore Resources'. The count is four; one URL identification was incorrect in the brief.",
      "implication": "The brief's preserved-content claim is corrected. The rebuild's CTA-content-fixtures table needs the redhawks.sharepoint.com URL as the Faculty & Staff branch, not /directory. The link target also opens in a new tab (target='_blank' at L165). Recorded for v17 amendments queue."
    },
    {
      "id": "E9",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "results.news.ftl contains course-shaped residue: self-id comment and modifier class both say 'course(s)'",
      "evidence": "results.news.ftl:47 `<!-- results.courses::GenericView -->` (the self-identifier comment) and L48 `<article class='listing-item listing-item--course listing-item--background-grey10 listing-item--color-black dataListing newsData'>` (the `listing-item--course` modifier class). The file's filename is results.news.ftl, the data-class suffix is newsData, but the modifier class and self-id comment both say 'course'.",
      "implication": "CSS selectors that target `.listing-item--course` would apply to news results \u2014 that is, news result cards inherit course-card styling whether intentionally or by residue. The rebuild should establish modifier-class-per-content-type as a clean contract; either rename to `.listing-item--news` or formalize the shared-with-course styling as a deliberate choice. The self-id comment is just dev-time tracking and is informational. Provisional E9 is confirmed via E.3 execution."
    },
    {
      "id": "E10",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "curator.ftl L31 stray double-quote after class binding",
      "evidence": "curator.ftl:31 `<article class=\"listing-item listing-item--promoted listing-item--background-grey10 listing-item--color-black\" ${(exhibit.additionalProperties.class)!}\">`. The expression substitution `${...}` is unquoted in the source; the trailing `\"` appears immediately after. Output for an exhibit with a class value 'highlight' would be `class=\"listing-item ...\" highlight\">` \u2014 invalid HTML attribute syntax.",
      "implication": "Most browsers will tolerate the malformed attribute by treating 'highlight' as a boolean attribute and discarding the stray `\"` (with possibly varying outcomes per browser). Functionally bounded but a markup defect. The rebuild should escape the expression and quote it correctly."
    },
    {
      "id": "E11",
      "category": "DEAD_IMPORT",
      "title": "auto_complete namespace has zero textual invocations \u2014 closes Phase C C8 definitively",
      "evidence": "grep for `@auto_complete\\.` across all 27 in-scope templates returns no matches. The Configuration macro in auto_complete.ftl (which initializes Twitter Typeahead via `jQuery('#query').autocompletion({...})` with datasets configured from stencils.auto-completion.* profile config) is never invoked from any reached site. The import at partial.ftl:52 binds the namespace but no consumer references it.",
      "implication": "Twitter Typeahead is fully dead code on Seattle University's template set. Combined with Phase C Finding C10's enumeration of the universal-stencils-cluster (which includes the Typeahead bundle at typeahead.bundle.min.js loaded from cdnjs), the Typeahead bundle becomes a CONFIRMED strip-out candidate for the rebuild's universal-stencils-cluster experiment. Closes Phase C C8. Provisional E11 in brief v1.1 is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "id": "E12",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "tabs.ftl:249 calls @base.Result which is not defined in base.ftl",
      "evidence": "tabs.ftl:249 (inside the Preview macro) `<@base.Result result=result view=view question=parentQuestion/>`. base.ftl defines only the getCssID function (L17-19) and inputsForForms macro (L25-44); there is no Result macro definition. The tabs.Preview macro itself is uninvoked anywhere in the 27 in-scope templates.",
      "implication": "Latent defect: the call site references a non-existent macro. If anyone ever invokes tabs.Preview, FreeMarker will raise an error at template-compile time. Bounded today because Preview is unreachable. The rebuild should either remove the call site (Preview itself is an UNUSED_FEATURE candidate) or define the referenced macro. Likely intent: an analogue to the .main[<renderer>].Result dispatch chain, but written before the dispatch pattern was finalized."
    },
    {
      "id": "E13",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "counts.ftl mismatched <p>/</span> tags",
      "evidence": "counts.ftl:13 `<p class=\"counts\">` opens a paragraph. counts.ftl:63 `</span>` closes a span that was never opened. The `</p>` close tag is missing.",
      "implication": "Browsers will auto-close the `<p>` when they encounter the next block-level element or the parent's close, and will silently discard the stray `</span>`. Functionally tolerable but invalid HTML. Validator warnings expected. Minor markup defect; rebuild should fix."
    },
    {
      "id": "E14",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "tier_bars.ftl L19 has duplicate class attribute on same element",
      "evidence": "tier_bars.ftl:19 `<div class=\"tier-bar\" class=\"sr-only search-tier\">Fully-matching results</div>`. Two `class` attributes on the same element.",
      "implication": "HTML5 specifies that the FIRST class attribute wins and subsequent duplicates are ignored; browsers consistently follow this. The intended `sr-only` (visually-hidden) treatment for fully-matching tier bars is silently dropped \u2014 the 'Fully-matching results' label renders identically to the partial-match label. Behavioral inconsistency in current production: the partial-match label is visible (intended) but the fully-match label is ALSO visible (unintended). The rebuild should consolidate to a single class attribute and decide whether fully-match bars should be visually hidden or visually rendered."
    },
    {
      "id": "E15",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "facets.ftl:124 applies special-case capitalization to 'past week' / 'past month' facet labels only",
      "evidence": "facets.ftl L124-128: `<#if category.label?lower_case == \"past week\" || category.label?lower_case == \"past month\"> ${category.label?lower_case?split(\" \")?map(word -> word?capitalize)?join(\" \")} <#else> ${category.label} </#if>`. The two specific lowercase labels get re-capitalized to title case; all other facet labels render as-is.",
      "implication": "A label-normalization workaround targeting two specific date-facet category labels. Other date-facet values (e.g. 'past year', 'past 30 days') do not receive the same treatment and would render with whatever casing the backend emits. The rebuild should generalize: either backend emits normalized casing for all date-facet labels, or FE applies a consistent normalization function to the whole facet, not to two hardcoded values."
    },
    {
      "id": "E16",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "hero_banner.SearchForm references label[for='bannerQuery'] for an ID that does not exist as written",
      "evidence": "hero_banner.ftl L22 `<label for=\"bannerQuery\" class=\"visuallyhidden\">Search:</label>`. The label references id='bannerQuery'. The combobox div has id='autocomplete-search-combobox' (L30). The actual input element is emitted by auto_complete.concierge.Concierge (invoked at L39), and per auto_complete.concierge.ftl L29 the input id defaults to 'query' (or the value of stencils.auto-completion.input_id profile config). No element with id='bannerQuery' is emitted by any reached path.",
      "implication": "Accessibility seam contract is broken: screen readers traversing label associations will not find the input. Functionally the page is usable (the input has its own placeholder, the visually-hidden label is announced when the input gains focus only if the for/id pair matches, which it does not). WCAG 2.1 compliance concern. Either the label's `for` should target 'query' (or the configured input_id), or the input emitter should be reconfigured to emit id='bannerQuery'. Rebuild should normalize the contract \u2014 likely best to have the label live near the input emitter rather than in the wrapper template."
    },
    {
      "id": "E17",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Five inactive renderer namespaces are structurally callable but functionally inert",
      "evidence": "partial.ftl imports results.video.ftl (L75), results.facebook.ftl (L76), results.events.ftl (L77), results.twitter.ftl (L78), results.instagram.ftl (L79). The renderer-dispatch logic in result_list.ftl:65-91 looks up `stencils.template.result.${result.collection}` and `stencils.template.result.${gscope}` in profile config to name a namespace, then invokes `.main[<name>].Result` if defined. Per Vic, no crawler feeds these five content types on Seattle U's collection set. The .main lookup remains structurally callable; the input never produces results that would route to it.",
      "implication": "The five inactive imports are functionally inert under current crawler configuration but structurally callable. If a future crawler change introduced (e.g.) a 'video' collection or gscope and profile config was updated to point at the 'video' namespace, the renderer would activate without code changes. The rebuild should: (a) decide whether to retain the renderer-dispatch pattern (carrying the cost of having structurally-inert imports as configuration-extension points), or (b) commit to explicit per-content-type renderer wiring and drop the dispatch indirection."
    },
    {
      "id": "E18",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Tab-conditional CTA region contains product-fixed REQUIRED content",
      "evidence": "partial.ftl L130-172 emits the promotional CTA region. Heading, body text, link URL, and button text vary by selected tab. Defaults to '/visit Visit our Campus'. Programs branch: '/academics/all-programs Discover Programs'. Faculty & Staff: SharePoint URL Redhawk Hub Explore Resources. News: '/newsroom Latest Updates The Newsroom'. All values are inline string literals in the template.",
      "implication": "Content-fixture rebuild requirement: the rebuild needs an externalized representation of these CTA values (likely a per-tab CMS-managed copy block, or a config table) rather than inline FTL string literals. Content is product-decision REQUIRED \u2014 changes require product sign-off. Where the values live should be a rebuild decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "E19",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Renderer dispatch profile-config key: stencils.template.result.${result.collection}",
      "evidence": "result_list.ftl:65 `<#assign resultDisplayLibrary = question.getCurrentProfileConfig().get(\"stencils.template.result.${result.collection}\")!\"\" />`. Fallback at L70 walks gscopesSet trying `stencils.template.result.${gscope}`.",
      "implication": "FUNNELBACK_PROFILE_CONFIG dependency. The rebuild needs to either: (a) replicate this profile-config key in its config layer, (b) drop the dispatch indirection and use explicit per-collection routing in code, or (c) preserve the FTL dispatch pattern and consume the profile config through it. This is the single key that determines which renderer markup template gets invoked for each result row."
    },
    {
      "id": "E20",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Cross-renderer markup-envelope shared contract: listing-item BEM envelope plus per-renderer modifier and data-class",
      "evidence": "All five renderers (results.ftl fallback + four active) emit `<article class='listing-item listing-item--<modifier> listing-item--background-grey10 listing-item--color-black dataListing <typeData>' data-fb-result='${result.indexUrl}'>` with the inner structure: `.listing-item__content > .listing-item__header > h3.listing-item__title > a.listing-item__title-link > .listing-item__body > .listing-item__summary > .listing-item__footer > .listing-item__footer-block`. Variations: modifier class (--generic, --course, --program, --people; note --course on news renderer per E9), data-class suffix (genericData, lawData, newsData, programData, peopleData), optional .listing-item__image-wrapper before .listing-item__content, optional .listing-item__subtitle inside __header, footer content per-renderer.",
      "implication": "The shared envelope is a stable contract for the rebuild. CSS rules likely select on `.listing-item` (envelope), `.listing-item--<modifier>` (per-renderer styling), and `.<typeData>` (dataListing.dataListing.newsData etc. \u2014 JS hooks). The rebuild can either preserve this contract verbatim (low CSS risk) or refactor into a normalized component shape (higher CSS migration cost). The `dataListing` suffix appears redundant with `.listing-item` \u2014 possible cleanup."
    },
    {
      "id": "E21",
      "category": "CONTRACT_SURFACE",
      "title": "Curator 'promoted' label is lowercase, not uppercase as CLAUDE.md framing implied",
      "evidence": "curator.ftl:41 `<span class=\"listing-item__promoted-tag\">promoted</span>`. The literal text is lowercase 'promoted'.",
      "implication": "Visual rendering relies on CSS text-transform to uppercase the label if 'PROMOTED' is the intended display. The CLAUDE.md briefing referenced this as 'PROMOTED' which is the display value (presumably text-transform: uppercase applied via CSS). For rebuild content fidelity: the source string is lowercase. Either the CSS transform is the contract (rebuild keeps lowercase source + CSS uppercase) or the source string should be normalized to 'PROMOTED' literal. Note for v17 project instructions amendments queue."
    },
